{"url": "https://www.indiehackers.com/post/whats-the-best-way-to-sell-a-client-side-javascript-library-816ebc9a7c", "title": "What's the best way to sell a client-side JavaScript library?@@Stripe", "meta_desc": "Hey IH, I'm working on a new project that will be distributed as a piece of client-side JavaScript code. Based on a recent Twitter poll I think Gumroad...", "viewport": "width=device-width, initial-scale=1", "charset": "utf-8", "h1": "\n          What's the best way to sell a client-side JavaScript library?\n        ", "h4": "\n      Community\n    @@\n      Products\n    @@\n      Learn\n    ", "canonical": "https://www.indiehackers.com/post/whats-the-best-way-to-sell-a-client-side-javascript-library-816ebc9a7c", "og:description": "Hey IH, I'm working on a new project that will be distributed as a piece of client-side JavaScript code. Based on a recent Twitter poll I think Gumroad...", "og:image": "https://storage.googleapis.com/indie-hackers.appspot.com/shareable-images/posts/816ebc9a7c", "og:image:height": "840", "og:image:width": "1680", "og:site_name": "Indie Hackers", "og:title": "What's the best way to sell a client-side JavaScript library?", "og:type": "article", "og:url": "https://www.indiehackers.com/post/whats-the-best-way-to-sell-a-client-side-javascript-library-816ebc9a7c", "twitter:card": "summary_large_image", "twitter:description": "Hey IH, I'm working on a new project that will be distributed as a piece of client-side JavaScript code. Based on a recent Twitter poll I think Gumroad...", "twitter:image": "https://storage.googleapis.com/indie-hackers.appspot.com/shareable-images/posts/816ebc9a7c", "twitter:site": "@IndieHackers", "twitter:title": "What's the best way to sell a client-side JavaScript library?", "body_text": "\n     \n \n \n     \n   \n     \n       Explore \n     \n   \n     \n \n \n     \n   \n        Community\n         \n \n \n       Connect with other founders and creators. \n        Explore\n         \n \n \n       Browse the best of Indie Hackers. \n        Products\n         \n \n \n       See what everyone's working on. \n        Podcasts\n         \n \n \n       Learn while you're on the go. \n        Meetups\n         \n \n \n       Meet indie hackers across the globe. \n        Store\n         \n \n \n       Buy an Indie Hackers t-shirt. \n        Newsletter\n         \n \n \n       \n        Stay up-to-date in 5 minutes or less.\n       Log In Sign Up \n                3 Comments\n               Report David Miranda Hey IH, I'm working on  a new project  that will be distributed as a piece of client-side JavaScript code. Based on  a recent Twitter poll  I think Gumroad is the obvious platform to sell it on. However, I can't shake the thought that there must be a better option than Gumroad by now. \ud83d\ude15 My ideal platform would let me create a SaaS by just uploading my script. It would let me: Upload a script and version it (v1, v1.1, v2, etc) Specify a few options my users can fill in (these will be passed into the script) And it would let my clients: Pay a monthly fee for access to the script Specify websites they own (i.e. the valid websites the script can be loaded) Can fill in the options that I chose for them (which will be passed into the script) \ud83c\udf89 Then they copy & paste the resulting code into their website (Wordpress, Ghost, Webflow, etc.) \u2014 and they get a working version of my paid plugin! I'd pay $40/month + a fee on every transaction for a no-headaches SaaS platform like this. I upload a script and don't have to worry about anything else! Does anything like this exist? \ud83d\ude4f I'd rather not spend 3+ months building it out with a SaaS starter template. \n          David Miranda\n         April 30, 2022 \n       \n \n \n \n\n 2 \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n\n              Not aware of anything that handles this. \n For  CropGuide  an image crop script we built it ourselves which is indeed a hassle. \n I\u2019d recommend  Paddle over Gumroad as the Gumroad API is kind of a mess. You could also investigate using LemonSqueezy. \n If the script is fully client side the alternative is selling the script itself with some sort of configurator app. You could then use Gumroad and upload the script there for your customers to download. \n\n \n\n\n     \n               \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n\n         \n          rikschennink\n         \n\n \n    \n\n \n \n \n\n       \u00b7 \n           4 hours ago\n \n \n           \u00b7 \n             \n              Reply\n             \n\n \n \n     \n\n\n \n \n\n \n         \n     \n       \n \n \n \n\n 1 \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n\n              As far as I'm aware, there is no service that meets all the above requirements. That being said, have you tried building a custom solution? Each script could have an embedded API key, if the user is subscribed, it'll run, otherwise it wont. \n\n \n\n\n     \n               \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n\n         \n          mjsmmry\n         \n\n \n    \n\n \n \n \n\n       \u00b7 \n           2 hours ago\n \n \n           \u00b7 \n             \n              Reply\n             \n\n \n \n     \n\n\n \n \n\n \n         \n     \n       \n \n \n \n\n 1 \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n\n              I'm not aware of any exiting marketplace that checks all of these boxes. Maybe that's because it's too niche of a market or folks don't actually like \"buying\" scripts. \n That said, charging a monthly fee for access to a bit of software is a different question. And I think you are on to something. \n My vote is to build out exactly what you need  on top of Polite Pop . Versioning, SaaS payments, website authorization, and API key population. But with one caveat: keep the code generic enough where you could copy-paste it out into the SaaS you are dreaming of with little modification. \n This lets you test two things: do people want to buy Polite Pop and is there interest marketplace interest scripts charging a monthly fee. \n I also have a ton of ideas on how the actual payment/verification could work but I don't want this comment to lose its main focus. Best of luck on this David, this sounds really exciting! \n\n \n\n\n     \n               \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n\n         \n          joemasilotti\n         \n\n \n    \n\n \n \n \n\n       \u00b7 \n           6 hours ago\n \n \n           \u00b7 \n             \n              Reply\n             \n\n \n \n     \n\n\n \n \n\n \n         \n     \n             \n              I Did Something Fun On My 404 Page\n             \n             \n                  \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n              74 comments\n               \n \n \n             \n           \n             \n              Launching over and over again\n             \n             \n                  \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n              21 comments\n               \n \n \n             \n           \n             \n              2 years for $6/MRR. 100% worth it\n             \n             \n                  \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n              16 comments\n               \n \n \n             \n           \n             \n              Is the Shopify app marketplace saturated? There is room for better apps!\n             \n             \n                  \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n              8 comments\n               \n \n \n             \n           \n             \n              A Dropout's Guide to Self Education\n             \n             \n                  \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n              6 comments\n               \n \n \n             \n           \n             \n              Your product\u2019s worth is a matter of context\n             \n             \n                  \n   \n     \n\n   \n \n              5 comments\n               \n \n \n             \n           Stay informed as an indie hacker. Market insights that help you start and grow your business. Subscribe by at \n      Learn from the founders behind hundreds of profitable online businesses, and connect with others who are start